{
  "text": "A thorough history should be taken when dealing with a pruritic case. Signalment of a case is obviously important (age, breed, sex etc), but much of what needs to be acquired can be ascertained from asking the following six questions [CITATION_1] : \u25a0 \u25a0 Is the horse actually pruritic? Pruritus often presents with chewing/biting, stamping or rubbing. This can be focal or generalised in distribution, with many secondary skin changes appearing from self-inflicted trauma.",
